   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : ">Isn't the best solution for the file-writing RPCs to return the file in the HTTP response, instead of writing to disk?\r\n\r\nYes, but JSON-RPC is somewhat incompatible with this idea. For `dumptxoutset`, we could just say \"use REST instead\", but wallet features really need authentication and a trusted interface.\r\n\r\nWe could hex-encode the backup, but that's ugly and (in a simple implementation) uses more memory than it really should. A quick search doesn't turn up anything for \"attachments\" on JSON-RPC responses. :/",
      "created_at" : "2021-06-29T19:21:58Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/20866#issuecomment-870853390",
      "id" : 870853390,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/20866",
      "node_id" : "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDg3MDg1MzM5MA==",
